-- Kajima, Nippon Steel & Sumitomo May Develop Offshore Wind Farms
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2012-11-16T03:26:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-16/kajima-nippon-steel-sumitomo-may-develop-offshore-wind-farms.html
Kajima Corp. (1812)  and the engineering
unit of  Nippon Steel & Sumitomo Metal Corp. (5401)  may develop 500
megawatts of offshore wind power capacity in the next five
years, the two companies said in a  statement  yesterday.  Nippon Steel & Sumikin Engineering Co. and Kajima, a
Japanese general contractor, are studying ways to combine their
expertise in building offshore structures and wind power
stations to develop the offshore generators, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
